definitions.definition: The fruit of the date palm, Phoenix dactylifera, somewhat in the shape of an olive, containing a soft, sweet pulp and enclosing a hard kernel.
definitions.example: We made a nice cake from dates.
There were a few dates planted around the house.

definitions.definition: The addition to a writing, inscription, coin, etc., which specifies the time (especially the day, month, and year) when the writing or inscription was given, executed, or made.
definitions.example: the date of a letter, of a will, of a deed, of a coin, etc.

definitions.definition: A specific day in time at which a transaction or event takes place, or is appointed to take place; a given point of time.
definitions.example: Do you know the date of the wedding?
You may need that at a later date.

definitions.definition: Given or assigned length of life; duration.

definitions.example: I arranged a date with my Australian business partners.

definitions.definition: One's companion for social activities or occasions.
definitions.example: I brought Melinda to the wedding as my date.

definitions.definition: A romantic meeting or outing with a lover or potential lover, or the person so met.
definitions.example: The cinema is a popular place to take someone on a date.

definitions.definition: To note the time or place of writing or executing; to express in an instrument the time of its execution.
definitions.example: to date a letter, a bond, a deed, or a charter

definitions.definition: To note or fix the time of (an event); to give the date of.
To determine the age of something.
definitions.example: to date the building of the pyramids

definitions.definition: To take (someone) on a date, or a series of dates.
(by extension) To have a steady relationship with; to be romantically involved with.
(by extension) To have a steady relationship with each other; to be romantically involved with each other.
definitions.example: They met a couple of years ago, but have been dating for about five months.

definitions.definition: To make or become old, especially in such a way as to fall out of fashion, become less appealing or attractive, etc.
definitions.example: The comedian dated himself by making quips about bands from the 1960s.

definitions.definition: (with from) To have beginning; to begin; to be dated or reckoned.
